properties.title: Baoneng Center
properties.extract:
The Baoneng Center is a supertall skyscraper in Shenzhen, Guangdong, China. It is 328 metres (1,076.1 ft) tall. Construction started in 2014 and was completed in 2020.
The architecture firm Aedas designed Baoneng Center for Baoneng Group.

properties.title: Dongmen, Shenzhen
properties.extract: Dongmen (simplified Chinese: 东门; traditional Chinese: 東門; pinyin: Dōngmén; Jyutping: dung1 mun4; lit. "East Gate") is a subdistrict within Luohu District of Shenzhen, in China. It is a shopping district located on Dongmen Pedestrian Street (东门步行街; 東門步行街; Dōngmén Bùxíngjiē; dung1 mun4 bou6 hang4 gaai1).
properties.name: Dongmen, Shenzhen
properties.short_description: Commercial area in Luohu District, Shenzhen, China

properties.extract: Hongling North station (simplified Chinese: 红岭北站; traditional Chinese: 紅嶺北站; pinyin: Hónglǐng Běi Zhàn; Jyutping: hung4 ling5 bak1 zaam6) is a station of Shenzhen Metro Line 7 and Line 9. It opened on 28 October 2016.

properties.title: Hongling South station
properties.extract: Hongling South station (simplified Chinese: 红岭南站; traditional Chinese: 紅嶺南站; pinyin: Hónglǐng Nán Zhàn; Jyutping: hung4 ling5 naam4 zaam6) is a metro station of Shenzhen Metro Line 9. It opened on 28 October 2016. This station is located under the southeast of the intersection of Hongling South Road and Shennan East Road. The station is an indirect interchange with Line 1 and Line 2 at Grand Theater Station.

properties.title: Hongling station
properties.extract: Hongling station (simplified Chinese: 红岭站; traditional Chinese: 紅嶺站; pinyin: Hónglǐng Zhàn; Jyutping: hung4 ling5 zaam6) is a station on Line 3 and Line 9 of the Shenzhen Metro. It opened on 28 June 2011 and Line 9 platforms were added on 28 October 2016. Line 3 station is located on Hongli Road, Futian District. Line 9 station is located on Hongling Middle Road, the boundary between Luohu and Futian.

properties.title: Luohu, Shenzhen
properties.extract: Luohu District is a district of Shenzhen, China, located north of the New Territories of Hong Kong, east of Futian District, southeast of Longgang District, southwest of Pingshan District, and west of Yantian District. It is one of the oldest parts of the city, having represented Shenzhen as a fishing village before 1953 and a market town from 1953 to 1979, when Bao'an County was promoted to a prefecture-level city and renamed Shenzhen.
properties.name: Luohu, Shenzhen

properties.title: Shun Hing Square
properties.extract: Shun Hing Square (Chinese: 信兴广场), also known as "Di Wang Tower" (地王大厦) is a 384-meter (1,260 ft)-tall skyscraper in Shenzhen, Guangdong province, China. Upon its completion in 1996, it became the tallest building in China, until being surpassed by CITIC Plaza in the next year.
